{
  "name": "\ud83d\ude80 Enterprise Multi-LLM Router with Fallback + Cost Analytics",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Multi-LLM Router\n**Flow:**\n1. Webhook receives `{ prompt, ... }` + `x-signature` header\n2. HMAC signature verified against `WEBHOOK_SECRET`\n3. Prompt scored for complexity (code/reasoning/math/length)\n4. Routed to one of 4 tiers: critical \u2192 Claude Opus, high \u2192 GPT-4, medium \u2192 GPT-3.5, low \u2192 GPT-3.5 (fast path)\n5. Every model call normalizes its response shape before logging cost/latency to InfluxDB\n6. On any model failure, falls back to the next cheaper/faster model rather than erroring out\n\n**Required env vars:** ANTHROPIC_API_KEY, OPENAI_API_KEY, INFLUXDB_URL, INFLUXDB_TOKEN, WEBHOOK_SECRET\n\n**Note on HMAC:** this version computes the signature with Node's built-in `crypto` module (available in n8n Code nodes) instead of CryptoJS, which is not bundled by default.",
        "height": 460,
        "width": 420
      },
      "name": "Sticky Note - Overview",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        200,
        -180
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "trigger-webhook",
      "name": "Webhook Trigger",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.webhook",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        250,
        300
      ],
      "parameters": {
        "httpMethod": "POST",
        "path": "llm-router",
        "responseMode": "responseNode",
        "options": {
          "rawBody": true
        }
      },
      "webhookId": "llm-router-v2"
    },
    {
      "id": "hmac-verify",
      "name": "HMAC Signature Verify",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        450,
        300
      ],
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const crypto = require('crypto');\n\nconst item = $input.first().json;\nconst rawBody = item.body || {};\nconst signatureHeader = $request?.headers?.['x-signature'] || item.headers?.['x-signature'] || '';\nconst secret = $env.WEBHOOK_SECRET || '';\n\nconst payloadString = typeof rawBody === 'string' ? rawBody : JSON.stringify(rawBody);\nconst expected = crypto.createHmac('sha256', secret).update(payloadString).digest('hex');\n\n// Constant-time-ish comparison guard against trivial timing leaks\nlet verified = false;\ntry {\n  verified = signatureHeader.length === expected.length &&\n    crypto.timingSafeEqual(Buffer.from(signatureHeader), Buffer.from(expected));\n} catch (e) {\n  verified = false;\n}\n\nreturn [{\n  json: {\n    ...rawBody,\n    verified\n  }\n}];"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "auth-check",
      "name": "Auth Gate",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.if",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        650,
        300
      ],
      "parameters": {
        "conditions": {
          "options": {
            "caseSensitive": true,
            "typeValidation": "strict"
          },
          "conditions": [
            {
              "id": "check-auth",
              "leftValue": "={{ $json.verified }}",
              "rightValue": true,
              "operator": {
                "type": "boolean",
                "operation": "equal"
              }
            }
          ],
          "combinator": "and"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "auth-fail-response",
      "name": "401 Unauthorized",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.respondToWebhook",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        850,
        500
      ],
      "parameters": {
        "respondWith": "json",
        "responseBody": "={{ { error: 'Invalid or missing signature' } }}",
        "options": {
          "responseCode": 401
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "prompt-analysis",
      "name": "Prompt Complexity Analyzer",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        850,
        200
      ],
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const prompt = $json.prompt;\n\nif (!prompt || typeof prompt !== 'string' || prompt.trim().length === 0) {\n  return [{\n    json: {\n      ...$json,\n      promptError: 'Missing or empty \"prompt\" field in request body'\n    }\n  }];\n}\n\nconst length = prompt.length;\nconst hasCode = /```|def |function|class |import |const |let |->/.test(prompt);\nconst hasReasoning = /why|how|explain|compare|analyze|reason|think step|l\u00f3gica|por qu\u00e9|\u00bf/.test(prompt);\nconst hasCodeRequest = /write |generate |implement |code|program|script|function/.test(prompt);\nconst hasMath = /integral|derivative|equation|solve|calculate|\\d+\\s*[\\+\\-\\*\\/]\\s*\\d+/.test(prompt);\nconst msgCount = (prompt.match(/\\n/g) || []).length;\n\nlet score = 0;\nif (length > 200) score += 1;\nif (hasCode) score += 3;\nif (hasReasoning) score += 2;\nif (hasMath) score += 2;\nif (msgCount > 5) score += 1;\nif (length > 1000) score += 2;\nif (hasCodeRequest) score += 1;\n\nlet complexity = 'low';\nif (score >= 6) complexity = 'critical';\nelse if (score >= 3) complexity = 'high';\nelse if (score >= 1) complexity = 'medium';\n\nreturn [{\n  json: {\n    ...$json,\n    promptLength: length,\n    hasCode,\n    hasReasoning,\n    complexity,\n    score,\n    requestStartedAt: Date.now()\n  }\n}];"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "prompt-error-response",
      "name": "400 Bad Request",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.respondToWebhook",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        1050,
        500
      ],
      "parameters": {
        "respondWith": "json",
        "responseBody": "={{ { error: $json.promptError } }}",
        "options": {
          "responseCode": 400
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "prompt-error-gate",
      "name": "Prompt Valid?",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.if",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        1050,
        200
      ],
      "parameters": {
        "conditions": {
          "options": {
            "caseSensitive": true,
            "typeValidation": "strict"
          },
          "conditions": [
            {
              "id": "no-prompt-error",
              "leftValue": "={{ $json.promptError }}",
              "rightValue": "",
              "operator": {
                "type": "string",
                "operation": "isEmpty"
              }
            }
          ],
          "combinator": "and"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "route-llm",
      "name": "LLM Router Switch",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.switch",
      "typeVersion": 3,
      "position": [
        1250,
        150
      ],
      "parameters": {
        "mode": "expression",
        "output": "={{ ({ critical: 0, high: 1, medium: 2, low: 3 })[$json.complexity] ?? 3 }}",
        "options": {
          "fallbackOutput": 3
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "claude-opus",
      "name": "Claude Opus (Critical)",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest",
      "typeVersion": 4.2,
      "position": [
        1500,
        -50
      ],
      "parameters": {
        "method": "POST",
        "url": "https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages",
        "authentication": "genericCredentialType",
        "nodeCredentialType": "httpHeaderAuth",
        "sendHeaders": true,
        "headerParameters": {
          "parameters": [
            {
              "name": "x-api-key",
              "value": "={{ $env.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY }}"
            },
            {
              "name": "anthropic-version",
              "value": "2023-06-01"
            },
            {
              "name": "Content-Type",
              "value": "application/json"
            }
          ]
        },
        "sendBody": true,
        "bodyParameters": {
          "parameters": [
            {
              "name": "model",
              "value": "claude-opus-4-7"
            },
            {
              "name": "max_tokens",
              "value": 4096
            },
            {
              "name": "messages",
              "value": "={{ [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": $json.prompt}] }}"
            },
            {
              "name": "temperature",
              "value": 0.3
            }
          ]
        },
        "options": {
          "timeout": 120000
        }
      },
      "onError": "continueErrorOutput",
      "retryOnFail": true,
      "maxTries": 3,
      "waitBetweenTries": 1500
    },
    {
      "id": "gpt4",
      "name": "GPT-4 (High)",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest",
      "typeVersion": 4.2,
      "position": [
        1500,
        100
      ],
      "parameters": {
        "method": "POST",
        "url": "https://api.openai.com/v1/chat/completions",
        "authentication": "genericCredentialType",
        "nodeCredentialType": "httpHeaderAuth",
        "sendHeaders": true,
        "headerParameters": {
